  91:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  92:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
  93:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     Use function HAL_USART_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
  94:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     weak function.
  95:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     HAL_USART_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
  96:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     and the Callback ID.
  97:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     This function allows to reset following callbacks:
  98:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
  99:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
 100:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
 101:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
 102:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxRxCpltCallback          : Tx Rx Complete Callback.
 103:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
 104:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
 105:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxFifoFullCallback        : Rx Fifo Full Callback.
 106:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxFifoEmptyCallback       : Tx Fifo Empty Callback.
 107:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : USART MspInit.
 108:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : USART MspDeInit.
 109:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 110:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 111:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     By default, after the HAL_USART_Init() and when the state is HAL_USART_STATE_RESET
 112:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 113:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     examples HAL_USART_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_USART_RxHalfCpltCallback().
 114:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
 115:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_USART_Init()
 116:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     and HAL_USART_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 117:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_USART_Init() and HAL_USART_DeInit()
 118:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 119:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 120:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 121:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_USART_STATE_READY state only.
 122:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 123:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     in HAL_USART_STATE_READY or HAL_USART_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
 124:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 125:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 126:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     using HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_USART_DeInit()
 127:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     or HAL_USART_Init() function.
 128:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 129:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 130:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     When The compilation define USE_HAL_USART_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 131:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     not defined, the callback registration feature is not available
 132:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****     and weak callbacks are used.
 133:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 134:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 135:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_usart.c ****   @endverbatim
